<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871023-0025 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Pansophic Systems Inc.</HL><DD> 10/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PNS </IN><TEXT>   Pansophic Systems Inc. said it expects to report flat to lower earnings for the fiscal second quarter ending Oct. 31, compared with the $3.6 million, or 21 cents a share, earned a year earlier.    The Oak Brook, Ill.-based computer systems company cited higher research and development expenditures, and efforts to build distribution capabilities associated with its recently acquired Applications Products and Graphics Products units.    Pansophic said it expects strong results for the second half. It cited strong revenue growth and said customer product trials were at record levels.    For the year ended April 30, 1987, the company earned $16.8 million, or 95 cents a share, on revenue of $114.5 million. </TEXT></DOC>